@rhtyd I remember Trillian having some issues when using ubuntu images, but cannot find the build failure. 
Will trigger a new one to investigate. 
@blueorangutan test ubuntu kvm-ubuntu

@adwaitpatankar this is because _resourceLimitMgr.recalculateResourceCount only recalculate the resource count on account(if accountid is set), or domain (if accountid is not set), not both account/domain.

We have this issue before, it is fixed by replacing _resourceLimitMgr.recalculateResourceCount with
```
                _resourceLimitMgr.decrementResourceCount(vm.getAccountId(), ResourceType.primary_storage, rootVol.get(0).isDisplay(), new Long(rootVol.get(0).getSize()));
```

_resourceLimitMgr.recalculateResourceCount is also used somewhere else, we also replace them.
